    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "you are filling a copy. Using ``inplace`` is an anti-pattern. Most operations will show a ``SettingWithCopyWarning``, but in this case this is a not easily detectable.\r\n\r\nUse\r\n\r\n```\r\nIn [11]: df[['C', 'D']] = df[['C', 'D']].fillna(-1)\r\n\r\nIn [12]: df\r\nOut[12]: \r\n          A         B         C         D\r\n0  0.236782  1.408896 -0.199882  0.803165\r\n1 -1.763881  0.232414 -1.000000 -1.000000\r\n2  0.878515 -0.394800  0.429696 -1.829569\r\n```"
  },
